Parts of Msunduzi will be without electricity during another planned outage on Friday and Monday. The affected areas will be cut off while the city’s electricity department is conducting work on the Retief and the Crossways primary substation. According to Msunduzi, the work will mainly consist of a change over from the existing 95mm cables to newly installed 630mm cables with a higher transfer capability. “This will improve the rating of each line from 13MVA to 26MVA between Retief primary and Crossways primary substations,” said the municipality. The estimated duration of work is 14 hours each day. The city also added that the outage will be regarded as a partial outage because one line will be switched off to conduct work while the other remains in service. Part of Hilton, Sweetwater, Knoll, Mbanjwa school and Enkangala will be experience power outages from 4:30 am to 6:30am and again at 9:30pm till midnight. Parts of Hilton towards Zayeka will experience power outages from 6:30am to 9:30am and again at 12am to 2:20am. Cedara, Mondi and nearby Hilton areas will experience outages from 9am to 11:30am and again from 2am to 4am. Hilton area and Hilton Gardens Hotel will be without power from 11:30am to 2pm. The hospital and Garlington Estate will be cut off from 2pm to 4pm. Winterskloof and parts of Hilton towards Zayeka will have power outages from 4:30pm to 7pm while Park offices, VCC, Queen Elizabeth Park and Worlds View will be left without electricity from 7:30pm to 9:30pm. Msunduzi urged members of the public to treat all electrical equipment and installations as live at all times.